div.p:
Being therefore provoked and stirred up, with these reasons; and having a little ease and rest from other affaires, I have attempted to make a LADDER, out of the Consideration of the Creatures; by which after a sort, GOD may bee ascended unto: And I have distinguished it into fifteene Staves or Steppes, after the similitude of the fifteene Degrees, by which men went up to SOLOMONS Temple;
      Eze. 40.


and of the fifteene Psalmes of DAVID his Father, Ps. 120. &c. usually called the Gradualls, or Psalmes of Degrees.
